Package: MortgageSurv
Title: Survival Analysis Models for Mortgage Default Prediction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Ana M", "Patrón Piñerez",
           email = "ana.patron@example.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Adapts survival analysis models originally developed in biostatistics
    to the context of the UK mortgage market. Provides tools for simulating mortgage
    loan data under a landmark Proportional Hazards Weibull framework, fitting
    dynamic landmarking models (LOCF), and comparing predicted default probabilities
    from Accelerated Failure Time (AFT) and Landmarking approaches. The event of
    interest is mortgage default, reinterpreting classical survival concepts within
    a credit risk context.
